            ">Alien Enemies Act block upheld</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/federal-appeals-court-blocks-trump-alien-enemies-act-march.png" alt="A federal appeals court has maintained a temporary block on President Donald Trump’s ability to use the Alien Enemies Act" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>A federal appeals court has maintained a temporary block on President Donald Trump’s ability to use the Alien Enemies Act. Credits: Saul Loeb/AFP/Getty Images via CNN Newsource
            </i></p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">A divided federal appeals court has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-28-03-2025-h1-1-upheld-a-temporary-block?source=website" target="_blank">upheld a temporary block</a> on President Donald Trump’s use of the Alien Enemies Act. Trump invoked this act, which gives him the power to remove undocumented immigrants. He used it to deport alleged members of a Venezuelan gang, Tren de Aragua. The DC Circuit Court of Appeals ruled 2-1, maintaining the block while legal challenges proceed.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">The ruling follows lower-court orders issued on March 15 by US District Judge James Boasberg, who temporarily blocked the deportations. Two flights carrying the deportees took off during the emergency hearing, leading people to believe the court ruling was intentionally ignored. The opposition claims the law’s application to gang members threatens to send them to countries where they face torture.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
